 at user worked crossings with long waiting times due to absence of information to the signaller on the position of trains (report 14/2011, Sudbury: published August 2011).</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:204pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Network Rail has developed, and is now testing, technology to enabl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">e signallers to identify the location of a train in a long signal section.</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:132pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The outcome of ongoing development work and trials is awaited.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4" style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:521.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Active level crossings</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style=