:Arial; font-size:10pt">Network Rail is implementing a programme to upgrade its highest ri</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">sk AOCLs.  The project is looking to upgrade about 72 (including all in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Scotland</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">) out of 110 AOCL crossings in total.  The upgrade consists of adding a modular barrier system to an existing AOCL level crossing.  Prototype installations are presently being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">trialled.  </span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:132pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The RAIB is keen to understand the outcome of these trials and the programme of ongoing installation.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:29.4pt"><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal">i.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:1